public interface PowerRate
extends java.lang.Comparable<PowerRate>, java.io.Serializable

Represents one measured power rate of a device under test at a certain point in time.

Author:
Claas Wilke

Method Detail

getPowerRate

long getPowerRate()
Returns the power rate of the device in mW. A negative value indicates discharging whereas a positive value indicates charging (typically discharging should be the case during energy testing).

Returns:
The power rate of the battery device in mW.

getTimeStamp

long getTimeStamp()
Returns the time stamp at which this PowerRate has been created in nano (10 ^ -9) seconds.

Returns:
The time stamp at which this PowerRate has been created in nano (10 ^ -9) seconds.

isPowerAdapterOnline

boolean isPowerAdapterOnline()
Indicates whether or not the platform under test is currently operated using a power adapter.

Returns:
If true, the power adapter is online.
